            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1269779773,
            "creation_date": 1269779773,
            "body": "<p>You're working with the value contained in it. If it is a mutable object then yes, it is possible to change the state of the instance of Class1 from outside, which violates data protection principles. This is why you should copy mutable types before returning them.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 2532891,
            "question_id": 2532881
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2d205a5ec26e812c3694335b819d68c9?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 79742,
